      "schema:name": "disclose-for-purpose",
      "schema:description": "Holo Privacy: obtain a W3C Verifiable Presentation that discloses ONLY the personal-data claims the user's standing policy authorizes for a given DPV purpose + recipient (IETF SD-JWT selective disclosure) — and can prove a fact (\"over 18\") without revealing the value behind it. Returns null when nothing is authorized (default-deny). Needs a connected wallet (the Holo Privacy app). Present the result to any tool that handles personal data.",
